{
 "name": "RPlog_Simon_the_Zealot_Simon_the_Martyr",
 "title": "Simon the Zealot, Simon the Martyr",
 "summary": "In the barracks of Karrde's base on Myrkr, Simon Sezirok returns from carving a rose into his wooden staff to find the Jedi Jessalyn Valios in tears, convinced she is a terrible Jedi who has endangered Talon Karrde's organization. Simon comforts her, showing her the carving as a symbol of her strength and absolving her of blame, then reveals he must leave: only he can keep Emperor Valak from hunting down Karrde's group, and he would rather face near-certain death alone than see Jessalyn killed. Steeling himself, he also confesses he has fallen in love with her, despite her fear that he is already turning to the Dark Side. Jessalyn pleads with him not to sacrifice himself, insisting love can hold back the darkness, and the two share a deep, surrendering kiss before Simon makes her promise to survive and not follow him.",
